# .ai-intern-rules
# Place this file in the ROOT of your target repository (not the ai-intern folder).
# The AI coding assistant will read it at session start and follow these rules strictly.
# Rename to `.ai-intern-rules` to activate.

## Stack
- Language: Python 3.11
- Framework: FastAPI
- Database: PostgreSQL with SQLAlchemy
- Tests: pytest

## Conventions
- Use snake_case for all variables and functions
- All API endpoints must have docstrings
- Never commit secrets or API keys
- All new modules must have a corresponding test file in tests/

## Workflow
- Always run `pytest` before marking a task done
- Use `black` for formatting before committing
- Branch naming: feature/*, bugfix/*, hotfix/*

## Off-limits
- Do not modify alembic migration files directly
- Do not delete any file in the `migrations/` folder
- Never use `SELECT *` in raw SQL queries
